  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2021-03-18",
    "date": "2021-05-04T14:03:11Z",
    "text": "Personal Health Investment Today Act of 2021 or the PHIT Act of 2021\n\nThis bill allows a medical care tax deduction for up to $1,000 ($2,000 for a joint return or a head of household) of qualified sports and fitness expenses per year. The bill defines qualified sports and fitness expenses as amounts paid exclusively for participating in a physical activity, including (1) fitness facility memberships, (2) physical exercise or activity programs, or (3) equipment for a physical exercise or activity program."
  },
